### Model diagnostics

#### Linearity and homoscedasticity


::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-28_73e35e3bc4cc80dd0cb665109eedfd76'}

```{.r .cell-code}
autoplot(qs_lm_02, which = c(1, 3),
                  colour = "#25d366",
                  smooth.colour = "#ef4836",
                  size = 1.5) + theme_minimal()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-28-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


Linearity assumption is violated

#### Normality assumption


::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-29_9bc9fb4f9a2d0b787283d71afb903e9c'}

```{.r .cell-code}
autoplot(qs_lm_02,
                  which = 2,
                  colour = "#25d366",
                  smooth.colour = "#ef4836",

                  size = 1.5) + 
  theme_minimal()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-29-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


Normality assumption is violated

#### Outliers and Influential cases


::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-30_8ae35ab9fad32197ea3833751eb489e7'}

```{.r .cell-code}
# outlier cases
autoplot(qs_lm_02, which =  c(4:6), colour = "#25d366",
                  smooth.colour = "#ef4836")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-30-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


There seems to be outliers in the data. Let's identify them in our dataset


::: {.cell hash='index_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-31_3357356c2863296ac5acc68279a0e475'}

```{.r .cell-code}
qs_outliers <- qs_lm_02 |> 
  augment() |> 
  rowid_to_column(var = "case_no") |> 
  mutate(case_no = as.character(case_no)) %>% 
 filter(abs(.std.resid) >= 3)|> 
 arrange(.std.resid)
qs_outliers %>% gt() %>%
opt_stylize(style=6, color="blue") %>% fmt_number(decimals=3)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
